{"questionId":"31036665","questionHtml":"<p>Solve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp;or equivalent&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to equate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>°</mo></math> to their reference angle&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>225</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mn>115</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em> if any additional solutions are seen.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"31036665","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.2","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Solve tan 2x-5°=1 for 0°≤x≤180°.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"2","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geomet